# Set Up ArgoCD for a Service

## Arguments
- `service`: Service name to add to ArgoCD
- `group`: Helm chart group the service belongs to
- `environments` (optional): Which environments to deploy to (default: all)

## Steps

### 1. Verify ArgoCD Application Set
- Check `k8s/helm/{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}/argocd/` contains the ApplicationSet template
- The ApplicationSet should auto-discover services via directory generator
- If using matrix generator, verify service's Helm chart path is included

### 2. Add Service to ArgoCD Values
- Update `k8s/helm/{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}/argocd/values.yaml`:
```yaml
services:
  {service}:
    group: {group}
    path: k8s/helm/{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}/{group}/{service}
    autoSync: true
```

### 3. Configure Image Updater
- Add annotation to service Helm chart `Chart.yaml`:
```yaml
annotations:
  argocd-image-updater.argoproj.io/image-list: >-
    {service}={{ .Project.Spec.Cloud.Region }}-docker.pkg.dev/PROJECT/{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}/{service}
  argocd-image-updater.argoproj.io/{service}.update-strategy: latest-version
```

### 4. Create Environment Overrides
- Ensure `values-staging.yaml` exists in the service Helm chart
- Ensure `values-production.yaml` exists in the service Helm chart
- ArgoCD applies the correct values file per environment

### 5. Verify Sync
- `argocd app list` — service should appear
- `argocd app sync {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-{service}-staging` — manual sync test
- Check that auto-sync policy is working

## Critical Rules
1. Never use `argocd app delete` without `--cascade=false` — it deletes the deployed resources
2. Always verify on staging before promoting to production
3. Image updater watches the container registry — ensure CI pushes images with proper tags
4. Rollback: `argocd app rollback {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-{service}-staging <revision>`

## Checklist
- [ ] Service added to ArgoCD values
- [ ] Image updater annotations configured
- [ ] Environment-specific values files exist
- [ ] ArgoCD detects and syncs the service
- [ ] Auto-sync policy verified
